                      <span>2001-11-29</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This book does not teach you the concepts of XSLT. Rather, it truly delivers on a promise of providing answers to common problems. While often books use code to only illustrate the concepts explained, "XSLT and XPath On The Edge" has tons of real world code, some of which I was able to use straight from the book(without changing a thing). <BR>I believe this book really helps to bridge the gap between just understanding the basics of XSLT and using it for real life, practical applications.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A book for when u need to do something.....</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
